- I hope you enjoyed your meal. - Yes, thank you. It was delicious.

00:36:00.816 --> 00:36:03.216
- Thank you so much. - Thank you. Have a good one.

00:36:03.286 --> 00:36:04.286
Sang Cheol!

00:36:04.886 --> 00:36:07.286
Were you just waiting for me to show up?

00:36:07.656 --> 00:36:09.686
Did you make some money tonight? Come on, buy a drink before you go.

00:36:09.756 --> 00:36:11.726
- No, I can't. - Come on, just one drink.

00:36:11.796 --> 00:36:12.796
This guy.

00:36:13.896 --> 00:36:18.236
I'll buy the beer, okay? I can't stop thinking of Byeong Ho.

00:36:18.566 --> 00:36:20.266
You think this is about the money?

00:36:20.706 --> 00:36:23.566
I can't get Byeong Ho out of my head either.

00:36:24.206 --> 00:36:26.306
If you and I start drinking together on a night like this,

00:36:26.606 --> 00:36:29.646
- we'll get in trouble. We can't. - Just one bottle each, okay?

00:36:29.746 --> 00:36:30.746
Mr. Kim!

00:36:32.546 --> 00:36:36.246
- I'll have a beer, too. - Ji Hyuk! It's been a while.

00:36:37.456 --> 00:36:39.116
All right, sure.

00:36:42.326 --> 00:36:43.386
What are you doing here?

00:36:43.826 --> 00:36:46.696
What? Can't you stand the sight of me?

00:36:46.796 --> 00:36:48.196
Who said I couldn't stand the sight of you?

00:36:49.066 --> 00:36:50.866
You're always jumping to conclusions.

00:36:51.696 --> 00:36:53.196
Good, if that's not the case.

00:36:53.636 --> 00:36:54.836
You just surprised me. That's all.

00:36:55.406 --> 00:36:57.336
You've never come to Yeong Bo's diner alone.

00:36:57.906 --> 00:37:00.106
Wow. Having Ji Hyuk here...

00:37:00.706 --> 00:37:03.106
really brightens up the place.

00:37:03.776 --> 00:37:05.076
It's been a long day at work.

00:37:05.816 --> 00:37:07.746
I was just going to grab a few beers to drink at home,

00:37:07.816 --> 00:37:09.486
but I saw my dad walk in, so I came in too.

00:37:09.546 --> 00:37:13.116
Of course. You carry a huge company on your shoulders.

00:37:13.416 --> 00:37:14.626
How could you not be exhausted? Right?

00:37:15.356 --> 00:37:18.126
Taking care of a family is tough enough.

00:37:18.756 --> 00:37:20.666
It's not like running a company is any easier.

00:37:20.796 --> 00:37:23.696
That's right. You've got to give it your all, Ji Hyuk.

00:37:24.336 --> 00:37:26.866
I was a real hotshot back at the brokerage firm.

00:37:27.336 --> 00:37:28.336
Right? But then...

00:37:28.736 --> 00:37:31.906
I quit, thinking I'd make a killing as a full-time investor.

00:37:32.406 --> 00:37:33.606
And you know what? I lost everything.

00:37:34.946 --> 00:37:37.146
So you've got to keep your head on straight, okay?

00:37:37.816 --> 00:37:39.216
Really? I didn't know that.

00:37:39.376 --> 00:37:42.846
Stop the nonsense. Kids these days can figure things out themselves.

00:37:45.256 --> 00:37:46.256
Come on, drink up.

00:37:48.486 --> 00:37:52.226
The kid's got enough on his plate, and this guy's nagging him.

00:37:52.856 --> 00:37:53.866
Putting all that pressure on him.

00:37:57.466 --> 00:37:58.536
Here, let me get that for you.

00:38:09.076 --> 00:38:10.076
Dad.

00:38:21.726 --> 00:38:22.726
Oh, that hits the spot.

00:38:48.386 --> 00:38:50.756
You've got an early start tomorrow. We should get going.

00:38:51.756 --> 00:38:54.056
Okay. Dad, I'll get this.

00:38:54.126 --> 00:38:56.426
No, leave it. I'll pay. Hey, I earn money too, kid.

00:39:11.676 --> 00:39:13.136
- Hey, Yeong Bo. - What?

00:39:13.206 --> 00:39:14.206
We'll settle up.

00:39:15.106 --> 00:39:18.446
- Hey, I said I was getting this. - Come on. Just let me pay.

00:39:18.816 --> 00:39:20.116
Gosh, this guy.

00:39:28.356 --> 00:39:31.095
I'm going to protest with a picket sign right out front.

00:39:31.096 --> 00:39:35.466
I'll say the mom who left her child is back to steal her liver.

00:39:35.766 --> 00:39:37.096
The surgery is in ten days.

00:39:37.636 --> 00:39:38.866
If you don't do this for him,

00:39:39.236 --> 00:39:40.366
your brother is going to die.

00:39:40.736 --> 00:39:44.176
- He is absolutely going to die. - If he dies,

00:39:44.476 --> 00:39:46.776
it's because you're his mother.

00:39:49.806 --> 00:39:50.816
That little witch.

00:39:51.746 --> 00:39:53.376
Am I supposed to just let Woo Jin die?

00:39:54.586 --> 00:39:55.816
But he really could die.

00:39:57.016 --> 00:40:00.116
With so little time left, this is truly a miracle.

00:40:00.786 --> 00:40:02.426
You found your long-lost daughter.

00:40:02.986 --> 00:40:06.826
Oh, no. If Woo Jin really dies, what am I going to do?

00:40:08.566 --> 00:40:09.866
What is all this I'm hearing?

00:40:10.836 --> 00:40:11.936
What do you mean, Woo Jin is dead?

00:40:12.836 --> 00:40:14.065
You lied to me while he was dying...

00:40:14.066 --> 00:40:15.336
because he needed a liver transplant?

00:40:15.866 --> 00:40:16.936
You lied to me!

00:40:18.176 --> 00:40:19.306
What was your motive?

00:40:20.036 --> 00:40:21.046
Hey, Ko Seong Hui.

00:40:21.876 --> 00:40:24.016
How could you do something like that as his mother?

00:40:26.276 --> 00:40:28.186
I don't even know who you are anymore.

00:40:29.316 --> 00:40:31.816
What are you going to do? Woo Jin is dead!

00:40:49.336 --> 00:40:50.336
No, that can't happen.

00:40:51.036 --> 00:40:52.176
If Woo Jin dies,

00:40:53.536 --> 00:40:55.076
I'll have nowhere to run.

00:40:57.246 --> 00:41:00.476
I'll be trapped like a rat in a cage with Park Jin Seok.

00:41:03.086 --> 00:41:04.086
I can't let that happen.

00:41:19.436 --> 00:41:20.736
Honey, what should I wear?

00:41:21.706 --> 00:41:22.706
What are you up to?

00:41:24.376 --> 00:41:27.646
I was thinking of wearing the watch we bought in Rome.

00:41:28.046 --> 00:41:30.676
- I have my book club today. - Right.

00:41:32.876 --> 00:41:33.876
One stack each.

00:41:34.586 --> 00:41:35.586
You really never change.

00:41:36.186 --> 00:41:38.756
Rather modest for a chairman's wife, don't you think?

00:41:39.316 --> 00:41:44.196
Excuse me? I have buildings, apartments, jewellery, and cash.

00:41:44.326 --> 00:41:45.426
I've got it all in here.

00:41:48.426 --> 00:41:51.296
I'll have to get you a gold bar. I don't see any in here.

00:41:52.736 --> 00:41:54.606
What would I even do with a gold bar?

00:41:58.106 --> 00:42:00.606
- Honey, have a good day at work. - Okay.

00:42:23.696 --> 00:42:24.766
We'll see about that.

00:42:40.516 --> 00:42:43.246
(Property Title Deed, Owner: Ko Seong Hui)

00:42:47.486 --> 00:42:49.356
After everything she's done to me,

00:42:50.356 --> 00:42:52.126
she has no maternal instincts whatsoever.

00:42:52.456 --> 00:42:54.696
Maternal instinct? Forget that. The woman has no humanity.

00:43:00.196 --> 00:43:01.506
Hey, it's okay.

00:43:02.566 --> 00:43:03.566
Come and join us.

00:43:06.206 --> 00:43:07.776
Eun Oh's a little conflicted, Ji Hyuk.

00:43:08.706 --> 00:43:11.416
The way she treated Eun Oh was subhuman,

00:43:11.616 --> 00:43:14.416
but she got her son surgery for an ear infection and raised him,

00:43:14.786 --> 00:43:17.986
and she's now doing the impossible to get him a liver transplant.

00:43:18.786 --> 00:43:19.856
So of course, you're confused.

00:43:23.026 --> 00:43:24.026
I can see why you'd be confused.

00:43:24.696 --> 00:43:25.696
But...

00:43:26.556 --> 00:43:27.566
Don't let it get to you.

00:43:29.366 --> 00:43:30.366
It's not like that.

00:43:32.096 --> 00:43:33.266
Hold on a second.

00:43:36.036 --> 00:43:37.036
Hello?

00:43:38.576 --> 00:43:39.576
Yes.

00:43:39.836 --> 00:43:41.406
Yes, this is the turnkey team manager.

00:43:43.706 --> 00:43:46.346
You want to commission us for the entire building?

00:43:46.516 --> 00:43:49.146
Yes. It's across from the Dosan Park.

00:43:50.086 --> 00:43:53.956
I see. When would you like to meet?

00:43:56.226 --> 00:43:57.726
You mean today?

00:43:58.726 --> 00:44:00.456
What? You're going to a meeting right now?

00:44:03.266 --> 00:44:04.736
I think I can be there by 2pm.

00:44:05.696 --> 00:44:08.266
Great, I'll see you then. Okay.

00:44:10.806 --> 00:44:12.206
Hey, what are you talking about?

00:44:12.936 --> 00:44:14.476
Why is a team manager going to the initial meeting?

00:44:15.106 --> 00:44:16.876
It's a complete remodel of a four-story building.

00:44:17.106 --> 00:44:20.916
Would you entrust a project of that scale...

00:44:20.986 --> 00:44:21.986
to a designer you haven't even met?

00:44:22.646 --> 00:44:24.416
Wait, you agreed to meet at the site?

00:44:24.786 --> 00:44:26.416
Yes. I'll be right back.

00:44:27.686 --> 00:44:28.686
Wait.

00:44:37.636 --> 00:44:39.166
The whole building?

00:44:43.766 --> 00:44:44.776
Nice.

00:44:49.306 --> 00:44:50.406
Welcome.

00:44:52.076 --> 00:44:55.446
I'm meeting someone. I'll order when they get here.

00:44:56.316 --> 00:44:58.316
They're already waiting for you over there.

00:45:17.506 --> 00:45:18.806
They locked the door from the outside.

00:45:19.576 --> 00:45:20.576
You can't get out.

00:45:30.486 --> 00:45:31.816
What do you think you're doing?

00:45:33.956 --> 00:45:34.956
Sit down.

00:45:36.486 --> 00:45:37.856
You just never quit.

00:45:39.196 --> 00:45:41.166
I can't give up, so no, it won't end.

00:45:42.196 --> 00:45:44.636
Not until one of us is dead.

00:45:45.866 --> 00:45:48.636
She really loves her son this much?

00:45:56.946 --> 00:45:57.946
In that case...

00:45:59.146 --> 00:46:00.816
Let me ask you something first.

00:46:04.716 --> 00:46:06.586
Why did you raise your son?

00:46:07.856 --> 00:46:09.626
Why did you only take him?

00:46:10.486 --> 00:46:11.996
And you even left your ID behind.

00:46:13.856 --> 00:46:15.366
I suppose you would be curious about that.

00:46:17.226 --> 00:46:18.236
Answer me.

00:46:24.536 --> 00:46:25.536
Well...

00:46:30.106 --> 00:46:33.546
(November 1996)

00:46:34.346 --> 00:46:37.986
Oh dear. If Woo Jin's ear infections keep recurring,

00:46:38.456 --> 00:46:40.056
it might be better to just go ahead with the surgery.

00:46:40.116 --> 00:46:44.296
- I'll have to ask their dad. - But wait, Seong Hui.

00:46:45.326 --> 00:46:47.456
Why do you always bring the twins in by yourself?

00:46:47.826 --> 00:46:48.966
You should come with their dad.

00:46:50.166 --> 00:46:52.496
You know how busy he is with his business.

00:46:52.996 --> 00:46:55.835
- We haven't eaten together in ages. - Mom.

00:46:55.836 --> 00:46:58.406
Leaving a beautiful wife like you alone all the time...

00:46:59.106 --> 00:47:00.506
That's a risky move.

00:47:01.876 --> 00:47:04.376
Oh, please. If I'm what you call risky,

00:47:04.716 --> 00:47:07.816
then your wife would probably make you close up shop.

00:47:08.416 --> 00:47:10.746
I'm not married.

00:47:11.316 --> 00:47:12.656
Do I look like I'm married?

00:47:15.026 --> 00:47:16.026
I need to take better care of myself.

00:47:17.126 --> 00:47:20.326
- So he really is single. - Mom.

00:47:20.556 --> 00:47:22.496
- Right this way. - Thank you.

00:47:22.566 --> 00:47:24.666
(Winter, 1998)

00:47:30.936 --> 00:47:33.506
Mr. Park Jin Seok is handsome, isn't he?

00:47:35.046 --> 00:47:36.276
So what if he's handsome?

00:47:38.976 --> 00:47:42.916
Are there any decent single guys among our regulars?

00:47:43.916 --> 00:47:47.186
And don't any of you get ideas just because Mr. Park is single.

00:47:47.586 --> 00:47:50.726
He got cheated on by his wife, so he won't even look at women.

00:47:54.626 --> 00:47:56.426
I hope you enjoyed the meal.

00:47:56.566 --> 00:47:58.596
- That was a wonderful meal. - Good.

00:47:58.996 --> 00:48:00.766
- Yes. - I hope you enjoyed everything.

00:48:00.796 --> 00:48:01.806
Yes.

00:48:03.736 --> 00:48:05.735
- Here you go. - Thank you.

00:48:05.736 --> 00:48:06.806
Keep the change.

00:48:08.076 --> 00:48:09.576
- Shall we? - Yes, let's go.

00:48:24.956 --> 00:48:27.396
Ms. Ko, this is Dr. Kang.

00:48:27.766 --> 00:48:30.296
I heard your husband passed away, and you moved.

00:48:30.796 --> 00:48:33.766
I was just calling to see if Woo Jin ever had his surgery.

00:48:34.336 --> 00:48:35.736
It's been on my mind.

00:48:36.336 --> 00:48:37.706
And with your husband gone,

00:48:38.106 --> 00:48:40.506
I've been worried about how you're getting by on your own.

00:48:49.016 --> 00:48:52.456
Hold on. Wait, Woo Jin. Here, Yu Ra.

00:48:53.056 --> 00:48:57.586
If you eat this banana and wait, I promise I'll be back with more.

00:48:57.856 --> 00:48:59.596
Let's go. Up you go.

00:48:59.856 --> 00:49:03.566
- Yu Ra! - Brother!

00:49:04.566 --> 00:49:05.996
I've been worried about you too, Seong Hui.

00:49:06.836 --> 00:49:09.266
I'll operate on Woo Jin myself.

00:49:11.136 --> 00:49:13.106
Wait! Please, just a second!

00:49:13.636 --> 00:49:14.706
Gosh, that crazy jerk.

00:49:15.446 --> 00:49:18.646
My son is sick! We have to get to the hospital!

00:49:19.276 --> 00:49:23.446
I can't be late. Gosh, I can't miss this opportunity.

00:49:29.626 --> 00:49:31.526
(Yongjin Hospital)

00:49:31.626 --> 00:49:32.626
Thank you so much.

00:49:36.426 --> 00:49:39.536
(Operating Room)

00:49:39.596 --> 00:49:40.696
The surgery was a success.

00:49:40.966 --> 00:49:42.866
He won't suffer from ear infections anymore.

00:49:44.236 --> 00:49:48.376
- Thank you so much, Doctor. - You look completely worn out.

00:49:50.246 --> 00:49:52.576
It's just so hard getting through each day.

00:49:53.446 --> 00:49:54.546
I can only imagine.

00:49:54.986 --> 00:49:56.216
You mentioned you don't have any family...

00:49:57.416 --> 00:49:58.416
around here, right?

00:50:01.986 --> 00:50:04.496
But with you helping Woo Jin like this,

00:50:05.096 --> 00:50:06.656
it feels like I have family again.

00:50:08.196 --> 00:50:11.436
It's not much,

00:50:11.966 --> 00:50:13.796
but I'd like to cook a meal for you.

00:50:14.506 --> 00:50:16.066
I'm sure you miss home-cooked food.

00:50:17.236 --> 00:50:18.836
I'll have home-cooked meals every day now.

00:50:19.276 --> 00:50:21.446
I went on a blind date recently, and I'm getting married next month.

00:50:22.406 --> 00:50:23.406
What?

00:50:23.976 --> 00:50:25.246
You're getting married?

00:50:25.546 --> 00:50:27.116
I've decided to open my own practice in Daegu.

00:50:27.316 --> 00:50:30.146
My fiancee's family is from Daegu. That's why I called.

00:50:30.416 --> 00:50:31.716
I just couldn't stop thinking about Woo Jin.

00:50:34.086 --> 00:50:37.126
In that case, you shouldn't have called at all.

00:50:37.386 --> 00:50:40.095
Come on, I've been treating Woo Jin and Yu Ra...

00:50:40.096 --> 00:50:41.396
for three years now.

00:50:49.106 --> 00:50:51.776
It was like fishing for minnows and catching a whale.

00:50:54.436 --> 00:50:55.646
You don't want to answer me?

00:51:02.116 --> 00:51:03.686
You have to hear my answer first.

00:51:04.316 --> 00:51:05.356
You said you were curious, didn't you?

00:51:13.896 --> 00:51:14.966
Then answer me.

00:51:15.596 --> 00:51:16.766
Why did you choose...

00:51:17.466 --> 00:51:18.566
to raise your son?

00:51:20.566 --> 00:51:21.936
I needed something.

00:51:23.536 --> 00:51:24.536
And?

00:51:25.076 --> 00:51:26.176
What was it?

00:51:30.176 --> 00:51:31.345
(Property Title Deed, Owner: Ko Seong Hui)

00:51:31.346 --> 00:51:32.846
It's the deed to this building.

00:51:33.576 --> 00:51:35.186
It's worth ten million dollars, even in a quick sale.

00:51:35.646 --> 00:51:39.686
The gift tax is 4.99 million, including the 10 percent local tax.

00:51:40.756 --> 00:51:44.256
Since you can't afford the gift tax, I'll give you that money, too.

00:51:45.026 --> 00:51:46.926
That's 2.274 million dollars.

00:51:48.566 --> 00:51:50.696
What is this?

00:51:57.066 --> 00:51:59.506
Here, 7.25 million dollars.

00:51:59.906 --> 00:52:01.106
Use this to pay the gift tax.

00:52:02.276 --> 00:52:04.206
Let's go sign the gift contract right now.

00:52:04.506 --> 00:52:06.846
I'll transfer the deed and give you this check today.

00:52:12.586 --> 00:52:13.716
Are you telling me...

00:52:14.256 --> 00:52:16.186
to sell you my liver?

00:52:17.886 --> 00:52:22.196
You refuse to give me what I'm owed, so I have to buy it instead.

00:52:23.326 --> 00:52:25.236
You seem to really care about your adoptive mom.

00:52:25.596 --> 00:52:28.166
Are you going to make her live in a rental forever?

00:52:28.906 --> 00:52:32.606
Donating your liver is simple. You're perfectly healthy.

00:52:33.836 --> 00:52:35.606
So you save my son,

00:52:35.906 --> 00:52:38.146
and I'll set your family up for life.

00:52:38.976 --> 00:52:39.976
Deal?

00:52:40.246 --> 00:52:41.586
Are you even human?

00:52:42.416 --> 00:52:45.086
Do you have any humanity at all?

00:52:45.786 --> 00:52:47.486
How can you be so completely...

00:52:48.056 --> 00:52:49.886
shameless and feel no remorse?

00:52:53.126 --> 00:52:57.026
I'm offering you life-changing money for your precious mom and brother.

00:52:57.396 --> 00:52:59.536
Money you couldn't have dreamed of in a million years.

00:52:59.796 --> 00:53:03.266
Do you realise how much I'm offering for a tiny piece of your liver?

00:53:04.436 --> 00:53:08.746
I offered 17.25 million dollars in total.

00:53:12.316 --> 00:53:14.786
So this is who you really are.

00:53:16.486 --> 00:53:18.056
Everything I saw before was just an act.

00:53:20.886 --> 00:53:22.686
Does anyone really have a "true self?"

00:53:26.896 --> 00:53:29.726
So you thought I was nice when you first met me.

00:53:31.536 --> 00:53:32.536
Eun Oh.

00:53:33.036 --> 00:53:35.266
People are like mollusks.

00:53:35.906 --> 00:53:37.466
There's nothing set in stone for people.

00:53:37.936 --> 00:53:39.676
A heart, a personality...

00:53:40.206 --> 00:53:41.576
Things like that don't exist.

00:53:42.606 --> 00:53:44.046
Just look at you.

00:53:45.116 --> 00:53:49.546
You'd let your brother die, yet you dare get angry at me.

00:53:49.786 --> 00:53:51.246
That's evil.

00:53:52.286 --> 00:53:54.826
Who are you to call me a bad person?

00:53:56.156 --> 00:53:59.326
This is why I can't stand people who aren't honest with themselves.

00:54:01.866 --> 00:54:03.826
That twisted logic of yours won't work on me.

00:54:05.366 --> 00:54:06.396
No, wait.

00:54:06.996 --> 00:54:08.706
You actually believe that, don't you?

00:54:09.536 --> 00:54:13.336
Enough of this pointless chatter. Let's go to the lawyer's office.

00:54:15.106 --> 00:54:16.946
Do you really think I'm going to accept this?

00:54:19.546 --> 00:54:21.276
Just because the building is worth ten million dollars?

00:54:22.616 --> 00:54:23.816
So you're refusing my offer?

00:54:25.756 --> 00:54:26.786
I'm not taking it.

00:54:29.656 --> 00:54:32.056
Are you crazy? Are you out of your mind?

00:54:32.626 --> 00:54:34.896
Why not? Because I deceived you?

00:54:35.396 --> 00:54:36.796
So your pride is hurt?

00:54:37.226 --> 00:54:40.366
Is it worth more than this money? What good is your pride, anyway?

00:54:41.136 --> 00:54:43.466
If I offered this to any match from the suitability test,

00:54:43.536 --> 00:54:45.006
people would line up for a mile.

00:54:45.476 --> 00:54:48.676
- You'd throw this away for pride? - No.

00:54:49.006 --> 00:54:53.716
My pride isn't worth this much. And neither is my liver.

00:54:54.316 --> 00:54:55.386
My liver...

00:54:57.086 --> 00:55:01.956
If someone said a boy was dying and asked me how much I'd charge,

00:55:02.256 --> 00:55:03.426
maybe I'd ask for 100,000 dollars.

00:55:03.986 --> 00:55:05.456
Or I might even give it for free.

00:55:06.326 --> 00:55:09.526
Do you still think this is about my pride?

00:55:10.396 --> 00:55:14.036
It's not. It's so I can watch you be ruined.

00:55:15.506 --> 00:55:17.805
Losing a multi-million dollar building...

00:55:17.806 --> 00:55:19.836
is a price I'll pay to stop you.

00:55:20.806 --> 00:55:22.576
It's a small price to ruin you, Ko Seong Hui.

00:55:27.976 --> 00:55:31.246
As for me, I can take care of myself just fine.

00:55:32.416 --> 00:55:34.656
Maybe you didn't have the confidence to raise your kids on your own,

00:55:34.716 --> 00:55:37.826
so you needed a rich man, but I'm not like that.

00:55:38.656 --> 00:55:39.726
My mom?

00:55:40.256 --> 00:55:41.926
I'll be the one to provide for her.

00:55:42.696 --> 00:55:43.896
I'll take care of her myself.

00:55:51.906 --> 00:55:53.306
What am I going to do?

00:55:55.876 --> 00:55:58.076
Because he was born to a woman like you,

00:55:59.046 --> 00:56:00.546
my brother...

00:56:01.786 --> 00:56:03.646
is going to die at 31. So that's how it is.

00:56:07.416 --> 00:56:09.826
Eun Oh. Don't.

00:56:10.756 --> 00:56:11.756
Feeling betrayed?

00:56:12.396 --> 00:56:13.926
That's nothing.

00:56:14.426 --> 00:56:16.496
You're just being young and naive.

00:56:17.196 --> 00:56:19.936
Go ask your mom if she's okay with you turning down ten million.

00:56:20.566 --> 00:56:23.035
Tell your brother you turned down ten million...

00:56:23.036 --> 00:56:24.366
to back out of the liver transplant.

00:56:24.706 --> 00:56:26.976
This is ten million dollars, Eun Oh!

00:56:27.506 --> 00:56:29.846
Your brother accepted one million without hesitation.

00:56:31.146 --> 00:56:32.916
You gave my brother money?

00:56:33.516 --> 00:56:35.716
That's not what's important right now.

00:56:37.516 --> 00:56:38.616
Your father...

00:56:39.216 --> 00:56:41.726
He died in a hit-and-run on his way to your first birthday.

00:56:42.756 --> 00:56:44.656
I was only 28.

00:56:45.296 --> 00:56:47.456
If I'd known I'd have twins for him to die in a hit-and-run,

00:56:47.526 --> 00:56:48.796
do you really think I would have married him?

00:56:49.626 --> 00:56:52.166
The lengths I went to just to raise one of you...

00:56:52.336 --> 00:56:54.166
You have no idea. You don't know anything.

00:56:55.606 --> 00:56:58.876
Please, let's just be realistic about this.

00:56:59.606 --> 00:57:01.476
Tell whoever locked this door to open it.

00:57:01.906 --> 00:57:03.176
Before I break it down myself.

00:57:08.986 --> 00:57:10.346
You really are a piece of work.

00:57:13.286 --> 00:57:14.456
If your brother dies,

00:57:15.186 --> 00:57:16.486
I won't let you get away with it.

00:57:18.396 --> 00:57:19.596
Can you handle the consequences?

00:57:52.296 --> 00:57:53.856
- Mr. Jo. - Yes?

00:57:53.926 --> 00:57:55.696
Is Ms. Ji coming back after closing the deal?

00:57:56.166 --> 00:57:57.266
Haven't you heard from her yet?

00:57:57.566 --> 00:57:58.696
No, not yet.

00:57:59.096 --> 00:58:02.136
It's a full building remodel, so the meeting's running long.

00:58:04.106 --> 00:58:05.106
(AP Group)

00:58:06.736 --> 00:58:08.746
(AP Group)

00:58:13.076 --> 00:58:15.086
(Apfel Kitchen)

00:58:20.616 --> 00:58:22.026
I'm sorry, Mr. Lee.

00:58:22.656 --> 00:58:24.126
It wasn't a client.

00:58:24.926 --> 00:58:25.996
It was her.

00:58:28.226 --> 00:58:30.926
- So she was just luring me out. - It was her?

00:58:31.566 --> 00:58:33.166
That woman is completely insane.

00:58:33.766 --> 00:58:36.036
This isn't the first time she's posed as a client.

00:58:36.736 --> 00:58:38.506
That's it. Give me her number.

00:58:39.136 --> 00:58:41.776
- Ji Hyuk. - I'll find her and end this.

00:58:42.946 --> 00:58:46.316
- This is my fight. - I thought we were a team.

00:58:47.176 --> 00:58:48.586
Can't I be the one to look out for you?

00:58:49.246 --> 00:58:51.856
Watching you deal with that monster all by yourself...

00:58:52.316 --> 00:58:53.416
I can't stand it anymore.

00:58:55.786 --> 00:58:58.396
You're already a great mentor to me.

00:58:59.026 --> 00:59:01.226
You've already done so much for me, and you continue to do so.

00:59:02.426 --> 00:59:03.496
But this...

00:59:04.426 --> 00:59:08.066
This is my cross to bear for being her daughter.

00:59:10.036 --> 00:59:11.536
If I need your help in the future,

00:59:12.076 --> 00:59:13.736
I promise I'll be the one to ask.

00:59:17.546 --> 00:59:20.016
I'm still going to check in on you, though.

00:59:22.386 --> 00:59:23.816
I won't hide anything from you.

00:59:25.886 --> 00:59:27.916
All right. I understand.

00:59:37.726 --> 00:59:38.796
Why did you call me here?

00:59:39.766 --> 00:59:41.736
I said I'd be here tomorrow. Why did you insist I come today?

00:59:44.806 --> 00:59:46.536
Because I want to see Yu Ra now.

00:59:49.006 --> 00:59:50.376
I'm her older brother.

00:59:51.746 --> 00:59:53.046
And I need to thank her.

00:59:55.216 --> 00:59:58.246
Can't you wait until after your surgery for that?

00:59:59.186 --> 01:00:01.016
What does that matter?

01:00:01.686 --> 01:00:04.026
You've gone decades without even knowing she existed.

01:00:06.956 --> 01:00:10.796
You won't let me and Yu Ra meet, even after the surgery.

01:00:11.766 --> 01:00:12.996
You're just using her for the liver transplant.

01:00:14.266 --> 01:00:16.736
- How could you do that? - For me...

01:00:17.436 --> 01:00:18.736
As long as you live, that's all that matters.

01:00:19.976 --> 01:00:23.376
She doesn't even remember you. You have no feelings for her, right?

01:00:27.116 --> 01:00:28.276
You're unbelievable, Mom.

01:00:28.846 --> 01:00:30.086
You're not human.

01:00:31.316 --> 01:00:33.156
If you really do that, I won't let it slide.

01:00:33.756 --> 01:00:36.226
My gosh. This is ridiculous.

01:00:39.496 --> 01:00:40.526
After the surgery...

01:00:41.996 --> 01:00:43.696
I'm going to tell Father.

01:00:45.436 --> 01:00:47.366
That I got a liver transplant from my twin sister.

01:00:52.006 --> 01:00:54.536
You might as well just stab me, Woo Jin.

01:00:55.746 --> 01:00:58.476
- The carotid artery is right here. - Mom!

01:00:58.546 --> 01:01:00.676
I even hid your transplant surgery, and you're going to tell him?

01:01:01.716 --> 01:01:04.746
If Chairman Park finds out about her, what will he do to me?

01:01:04.946 --> 01:01:07.656
Then I'll lose everything. Because I'll have lost his trust.

01:01:07.716 --> 01:01:08.726
And you'd still tell him?

01:01:11.356 --> 01:01:12.426
Mom,

01:01:13.826 --> 01:01:16.096
It's so unfair to Yu Ra.

01:01:17.426 --> 01:01:20.336
You can ask Father for forgiveness, can't you?

01:01:23.006 --> 01:01:24.836
Mom, if you don't promise me,

01:01:25.606 --> 01:01:28.036
I'm really not getting the liver transplant.

01:01:31.746 --> 01:01:34.176
As a matter of fact, she already refused the transplant.

01:01:36.946 --> 01:01:39.456
If I can't change her mind, you're going to die anyway,

01:01:39.716 --> 01:01:41.756
so don't you dare play games with your life.

01:01:42.026 --> 01:01:43.186
As if you'd actually let yourself die.

01:01:43.626 --> 01:01:46.096
You hear me? She said no!

01:01:46.756 --> 01:01:50.766
She's refusing since I'm the mother you say I am!

01:01:53.896 --> 01:01:55.136
Are you scared now?

01:01:56.006 --> 01:01:57.336
Now, you're scared, aren't you?

01:02:05.976 --> 01:02:07.776
So there is a way.

01:02:10.016 --> 01:02:12.786
Having you beg her yourself, Woo Jin.

01:02:38.176 --> 01:02:39.176
What's this?

01:02:46.516 --> 01:02:48.386
I sent you a heads-up so you wouldn't be scared,

01:02:49.656 --> 01:02:50.926
but here you are, ready for a fight.

01:02:53.026 --> 01:02:54.026
Han Woo Jin?

01:02:55.766 --> 01:02:57.526
Pretty dramatic entrance, right?

01:02:59.596 --> 01:03:00.596
Yes.

01:03:05.776 --> 01:03:07.436
I have a favour to ask you.

01:03:10.646 --> 01:03:11.646
A favour?

01:03:52.016 --> 01:03:54.556
(Our Golden Days)

01:03:54.956 --> 01:03:57.956
- I'm sorry I couldn't keep my word. - You're not moving out?

01:03:58.026 --> 01:04:00.895
- I'll move out when I'm married. - Married? What do you mean?

01:04:00.896 --> 01:04:01.966
Are you getting married?

01:04:02.026 --> 01:04:04.566
I want to go visit Woo Jin. I can just wear a disguise.

01:04:04.626 --> 01:04:08.436
The kind of people I hate most are deceivers. Liars.

01:04:08.496 --> 01:04:09.936
You lied to me?

01:04:10.166 --> 01:04:13.106
You said your awful birth mother only came for the liver transplant.

01:04:13.176 --> 01:04:15.746
Remember? That's what I'm here to ask for.

01:04:15.846 --> 01:04:17.776
This is the ultimate revenge I can get.

01:04:17.846 --> 01:04:19.245
That crazy brat...

01:04:19.246 --> 01:04:21.646
If he dies, I die too, Detective.

01:04:21.776 --> 01:04:23.786
This is the face of your brother you're about to kill.

01:04:23.846 --> 01:04:26.056
I want you to know exactly who you're killing.

01:04:26.186 --> 01:04:27.586
I'm not interested.